<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="866" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-05"><hi rend="italic">April 5,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">Confidential</hi>,<lb/>No.
                                966.</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to request that,
                            in case of trouble between Spain and the United States, the British
                            consul-general at Habana may take charge of the American property and
                            papers belonging to the American, consulate there, which will be turned
                            over by General Lee to him. I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>